Defendant Hakeem Dontrail Harris in court with attorney Ann T. Bowe.  Defendant Hakeem Dontrail Harris in custody.  Laura Ann Crivello appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: KAR.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the state, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Dextrisha S.

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 6 YEARS, with credit for 62 DAYS time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS with reception at Dodge Correctional Facility; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 3 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence.  The defendant IS ELIGIBLE for the Challenge Incarceration Program effective immediately and IS NOT ELIGIBLE for the Substance Abuse Program.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
1) Obtain an AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
2) Maintain absolute sobriety with random urine screens; No illegal drugs; No controlled substances unless by valid prescription;
3) Obtain/maintain full-time employment, full-time school or combination of both;
4) Complete 100 hours of community service during the period of extended supervision;
5) Provide a DNA sample;
6) Court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge to paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b). Any remaining balance upon release to extended supervision shall be paid by the end of extended supervision period; failure to pay will result in the entry of a civil judgment. 

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions: firearm and body armor possession and voting.

